    },
    {
      "id": "model-content",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 122.68061919544596,
      "y": -517.2053859888169,
      "width": 411.7494591562691,
      "height": 126.04575280293953,
      "fontSize": 10.083660224235162,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "Architecture: Microservices with message-oriented middleware\nCommunication: gRPC (synchronous RPC) between services\nCoordination: Bully algorithm for leader election among executor replicas\nFailure Model: Crash-stop (processes may crash, no Byzantine behavior)\nVector Clocks: [TransactionVerif, FraudDetect, Suggestions] — 3 services,\n                        7 events (A-G) tracking causal ordering across validation workflow\nReplication: 3 order executor replicas for high availability\nFault Tolerance: Automatic re-election when leader crashes\nScalability: Horizontal scaling via Docker Compose replicas",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 143,
      "strokeColor": "#868e96",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
